President Joe Biden delivered a commencement speech at Howard University, where he praised the graduates for their achievements and emphasized the importance of their role in shaping the future of the nation. He spoke about the ongoing battle for the soul of America, highlighting the need to confront racism, white supremacy, and political extremism. President Biden also addressed issues such as climate change, gun violence, police reform, and the importance of investing in historically Black colleges and universities (HBCUs). He encouraged the graduates to find a balance between ambition and happiness, and to continue standing for truth and right.